1602043200.title: Bargain Hunt
1602043200.descr: Two teams of amateur antique collectors meet at an antiques fair to compete to make the largest profit from a three hundred pound budget. Once the contestants have done the shopping for their own items, the experts then take any leftover money and go shopping for more antiques which is 'bonus buys'. The teams then have to decide whether or not to take these items to auction.

1602045900.title: Last of the Summer Wine
1602045900.descr: Clegg is writing his memoirs, but is having trouble remembering people's names; Clegg, Truly and Billy meet a man who wants to sail to Ilkley in an inflatable swan, unfortunately it has developed a puncture which Entwistle repairs; Clegg climbs a tree so he can see the church clock, unfortunately he gets stuck; Tom and Entwistle try to cheer Smiler up after he has been dumped by Hermione.

1602047700.title: Call the Midwife
1602047700.descr: Period drama series set in East London in the 1950s, following the life and work of a young midwife Jenny Lee and her colleagues at the Nonnatus House nursing convent. They serve the poor society of Poplar, London. Their main duty is to help bring safe birth to women and help them look after their newborns.

1602051000.title: DIY SOS: The Big Build
1602051000.descr: Take a family in desperate need of help in their home. Add some local tradesmen, lot's of generosity and a bucket load of community spirit. 1602095400.title: Doctors
1602095400.descr: Female police officer Jasmine catches Emma's eye, while frostiness between Al and Daniel continues. Rob gets help from the old guard in solving a hit and run case and Emma tries to calm an angry woman nursing old wounds

1602097200.title: Our Girl
1602097200.descr: Set in the time of Britain's withdrawal from Afghanistan, Our Girl follows the journeys of female medics. It all began when teenage girl Molly found herself in the army's recruitment office, after being sick in the doorway having celebrated her eighteenth birthday. Since then, there has been incredible displays of love, laughs, and loss.

1602100500.title: The Split
1602100500.descr: Drama by award-winning writer Abi Morgan with a major role for Barry Atsma. Talented divorce attorney Hannah leaves her family's law firm to work for the competitor Noble & Hale. This puts the relationship with her mother Ruth and her sisters Nina and Rose under great pressure.

1602103500.title: Live at the Apollo
1602103500.descr: Hammersmith Apollo Theatre hosts some of the biggest names in stand up comedy. Hosted by Jack Dee, performing his own sketches and introducing well known and loved acts such as Lee Mack, Michael McIntyre, Sean Lock and Sarah Millican. Running since September 2004, this showtime series is a classic comedy staple, drawing crowds in their staggering numbers to the theatre in West London, every year.

1602106200.title: Ordinary Lies
1602106200.descr: Drama and deceit lurks in every corner of the shop floor and office in Ordinary Lies, with employees concealing dark secrets from their coworkers. Each episode focusses on an individual employee and their personal tribulations, with their lies spiralling out of control and causing dire repercussions. Series one focusses on the workers at JS Motors, a car showroom, with series two focussing on Coopers Outdoors, a sports-goods store.
